            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>126900</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Φιλόκωμος"><seg part="I"><supplied reason="lost">Φιλ</supplied>οκωμ<gap reason="lost" atLeast="1" atMost="2" unit="character"/></seg></name></persName> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>ατ</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2a"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraduisible.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Not usefully translatable.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraducibile.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>غير قابل للترجمة بشكل جيد</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>The only clue is here the sequence of three letters at line 1, which leads to the personal name Philokomos, a rather common name in Cyrenaica. 
                   We cannot know at which case it was mentioned. Nothing can be guessed about the second line.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
